---
---

<section
  data-test="comparison-section"
  style="padding: 4rem 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);"
>
  <div style="max-width: 72rem; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.375rem, 3vw, 2rem); font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      The before and after
    </h2>
    <p style="font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 3rem; max-width: 40rem;">
      The same feature — "User Notifications" — described two ways.
    </p>

    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 26rem), 1fr)); gap: 1.5rem;">

      <!-- Without RootSpec -->
      <div
        data-test="comparison-without"
        style="background-color: var(--color-bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.75rem;"
      >
        <div style="font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          Without RootSpec
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          Slack thread from 3 months ago
        </h3>
        <div style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;">
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem; padding: 0.75rem; background-color: var(--color-bg); border-radius: 4px; font-style: italic;">
            "We need to add notifications. Users have been asking. Just do the basics — email when something happens. Should be quick."
          </p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.8125rem;">
            <strong>Story (in Jira):</strong> "As a user, I want to receive notifications so that I know when things happen."
          </p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            <em>No acceptance criteria. No rationale. "Something happens" is undefined.
            Three engineers interpret this differently. The feature ships with email-only,
            no user controls, and no way to turn it off. Support tickets begin immediately.</em>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
            Two months later: a re-spec, a rewrite, and a migration.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- With RootSpec -->
      <div
        data-test="comparison-with"
        style="background-color: var(--color-bg-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-accent); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1.75rem;"
      >
        <div style="font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          With RootSpec
        </div>
        <h3 style="font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          User story from the spec
        </h3>
        <div style="font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-text-code); line-height: 1.65; background-color: var(--color-bg); border-radius: 4px; padding: 1rem;">
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>id:</strong> US-204</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>title:</strong> User controls notification preferences</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>pillar:</strong> User Autonomy (L1 Design Pillar 3)</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>given:</strong> user navigates to notification settings</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>when:</strong> user disables email alerts for comments</p>
          <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem;"><strong>then:</strong></p>
          <p style="padding-left: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">- no email is sent on subsequent comments</p>
          <p style="padding-left: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem;">- in-app notification still appears</p>
          <p style="padding-left: 1rem;">- preference persists across sessions</p>
        </div>
        <p style="font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-top: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.6;">
          <em>Traceable to a design pillar. Acceptance criteria are testable. The story is the test.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
